  </ul>
  <h3 class="red">Later / Full Platform</h3>
  <ul class="red">
    <li>Full lead pipeline.</li>
    <li>Appointment calendar.</li>
    <li>Earnings dashboard and payout tracking.</li>
    <li>Client notes and intake responses.</li>
    <li>Availability slots.</li>
    <li>Auto-replies.</li>
    <li>Review management.</li>
    <li>Profile analytics.</li>
    <li>Document request templates.</li>
    <li>Subscription plan management.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Module 9: Admin Dashboard, Trust, Verification, and Moderation</h2>
  <p class="meta">Owner Type: Full-Stack Developer</p>
  <h3>Purpose</h3>
  <p>The admin dashboard is the trust backbone. It manages users, verifies advocates, moderates content, handles reports, and protects the platform.</p>
  <h3 class="green">Prototype / Build Now</h3>
  <ul class="green">
    <li>View all users.</li>
    <li>Search and filter users by role.</li>
    <li>Pending advocate verification queue.</li>
    <li>Approve/reject advocate verification.</li>
    <li>Edit user role/name.</li>
    <li>Send warning message.</li>
    <li>Basic platform stats.</li>
    <li>Reported posts placeholder/list.</li>
    <li>Hide/remove post action if possible.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3 class="red">Later / Full Platform</h3>
  <ul class="red">
    <li>Document verification workflow.</li>
    <li>Advocate suspension.</li>
    <li>Dispute management.</li>
    <li>Refund management.</li>
    <li>Review moderation.</li>
    <li>AI answer audit.</li>
    <li>Admin activity logs.</li>
    <li>Role-based admin permissions.</li>
    <li>Compliance dashboard.</li>
    <li>Data deletion/export requests.</li>
    <li>Legal escalation workflows.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Module 10: Advocate Verification System</h2>
  <p class="meta">Owner Type: Backend/Supabase Developer</p>
  <h3>Purpose</h3>
  <p>Verification builds trust. It ensures advocates are not presented as verified without admin review.</p>
  <h3 class="green">Prototype / Build Now</h3>
  <ul class="green">
    <li>Advocate submits Bar Council number.</li>
    <li>Advocate submits practice areas, experience, location, and languages.</li>
    <li>Verification status stored.</li>
    <li>Admin can mark Pending, Verified, or Rejected.</li>
    <li>Badge appears on profile, directory, and feed author card.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3 class="red">Later / Full Platform</h3>
  <ul class="red">
    <li>Document upload.</li>
    <li>Bar Council ID upload.</li>
    <li>Certificate of Practice upload.</li>
    <li>Manual review notes and rejection reasons.</li>
    <li>Annual re-verification.</li>
    <li>Suspended/debarred tracking.</li>
    <li>Verification audit history.</li>
    <li>External verification partnerships.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Module 11: AI Legal Learning Assistant</h2>
  <p class="meta">Owner Type: AI/Frontend Developer</p>
  <h3>Purpose</h3>
  <p>The AI assistant helps users understand legal issues in simple language. It must educate, not replace an advocate. Every answer should include a clear disclaimer.</p>
  <h3 class="green">Prototype / Build Now</h3>
  <ul class="green">
    <li>AI Q&A page.</li>
    <li>Simple input for legal questions.</li>
    <li>Safe response with disclaimer.</li>
    <li>Suggested topics.</li>
    <li>CTA to advocate directory.</li>
    <li>Basic query history.</li>
    <li>Prompt guardrails against definitive legal advice.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3 class="red">Later / Full Platform</h3>
  <ul class="red">
    <li>Backend-secured OpenAI integration.</li>
    <li>Retrieval-based Indian legal knowledge base.</li>
    <li>Citations and state-specific guidance.</li>
    <li>Hindi/Marathi support.</li>
    <li>Document summarization.</li>
    <li>AI answer audit logs.</li>
    <li>Hallucination detection.</li>
    <li>Urgent legal risk escalation.</li>
    <li>Advocate recommendation based on query.</li>
  </ul>

