  <h3 class="red">Later / Full Platform</h3>
  <ul class="red">
    <li>Razorpay integration.</li>
    <li>Payment gateway webhooks.</li>
    <li>Advocate payouts and platform commission.</li>
    <li>Refunds and cancellation fees.</li>
    <li>GST/invoice handling.</li>
    <li>Payment dispute handling.</li>
    <li>Subscription plans for advocates.</li>
    <li>Financial reconciliation dashboard.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Module 18: Notifications</h2>
  <p class="meta">Owner Type: Backend/Full-Stack Developer</p>
  <h3>Purpose</h3>
  <p>Keep users informed about consultation requests, messages, verification, posts, comments, follows, and mentions.</p>
  <h3 class="green">Prototype / Build Now</h3>
  <ul class="green">
    <li>Toast notifications.</li>
    <li>Dashboard notification cards.</li>
    <li>Notify when request is submitted, accepted/rejected, message received, and verification approved/rejected.</li>
    <li>Feed notification placeholder for comments/reactions.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3 class="red">Later / Full Platform</h3>
  <ul class="red">
    <li>Email notifications.</li>
    <li>SMS and WhatsApp notifications.</li>
    <li>Push notifications.</li>
    <li>Reminder system.</li>
    <li>Notification preferences.</li>
    <li>Calendar reminders.</li>
    <li>Mentions and follow notifications.</li>
    <li>Notification audit logs.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Module 19: Legal, Compliance, Trust, and Platform Policy</h2>
  <p class="meta">Owner Type: Founder + Legal Advisor + Product Manager</p>
  <h3>Purpose</h3>
  <p>This protects the platform legally and ethically. It is especially important because NyayaSetu handles legal information, public justice discourse, personal data, and advocate discovery.</p>
  <h3 class="green">Prototype / Build Now</h3>
  <ul class="green">
    <li>Basic terms page.</li>
    <li>Basic privacy page.</li>
    <li>AI disclaimer.</li>
    <li>Consultation disclaimer.</li>
    <li>Advocate verification disclaimer.</li>
    <li>Notice that NyayaSetu does not directly provide legal advice.</li>
    <li>Posting guidelines.</li>
    <li>Safe language across UI.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3 class="red">Later / Full Platform</h3>
  <ul class="red">
    <li>Full legal terms.</li>
    <li>DPDP compliance policy.</li>
    <li>Consent management.</li>
    <li>Grievance officer details.</li>
    <li>Refund/cancellation policy.</li>
    <li>Advocate agreement and client agreement.</li>
    <li>AI usage policy.</li>
    <li>Data breach response plan.</li>
    <li>Bar Council advertising compliance review.</li>
    <li>Community guidelines and content moderation policy.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Module 20: Analytics and Metrics</h2>
  <p class="meta">Owner Type: Backend/Product Analytics Developer</p>
  <h3>Purpose</h3>
  <p>Show traction potential and help the team make decisions. Investors need to see growth logic, not only features.</p>
  <h3 class="green">Prototype / Build Now</h3>
  <ul class="green">
    <li>Admin stats: total users, advocates, posts, consultation requests, pending verifications, AI questions.</li>
    <li>Mock growth numbers for pitch dashboard.</li>
    <li>Basic feed engagement counts.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3 class="red">Later / Full Platform</h3>
  <ul class="red">
    <li>MAU tracking.</li>
    <li>Conversion funnel.</li>
    <li>Advocate onboarding conversion.</li>
    <li>Consultation booking rate.</li>
    <li>NPS and retention.</li>
    <li>Response time tracking.</li>
    <li>AI usage analytics.</li>
    <li>Revenue dashboard.</li>
    <li>Cohort analytics and churn tracking.</li>
    <li>Content engagement analytics.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Module 21: Mobile App and Desktop Platform Readiness</h2>
  <p class="meta">Owner Type: Product + UI Designer + Frontend Lead</p>
  <h3>Purpose</h3>
  <p>The platform should be designed so it can become both a mobile app and a desktop web platform without rebuilding the product logic.</p>
  <h3 class="green">Prototype / Build Now</h3>
  <ul class="green">
    <li>Mobile-responsive web UI.</li>
    <li>Bottom navigation behavior planned for mobile.</li>
    <li>Desktop sidebar/top navigation planned.</li>
    <li>Feed, chat, directory, and dashboards work on small screens.</li>
    <li>Touch-friendly buttons and forms.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3 class="red">Later / Full Platform</h3>
  <ul class="red">
    <li>React Native or native mobile app.</li>
    <li>Push notifications.</li>
    <li>Deep links.</li>
    <li>App-specific onboarding.</li>
    <li>Offline draft posts.</li>
    <li>Mobile document scanning.</li>
    <li>Biometric app lock.</li>
    <li>Separate desktop power-user layouts for advocates/admins.</li>
  </ul>

  <h1>5. Recommended Team Distribution</h1>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Person</th><th>Focus Area</th><th>Responsibilities</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Person 1</td><td>Auth + Role Routing</td><td>Authentication, profile creation, protected routes, role-based redirects.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Person 2</td><td>Client Experience</td><td>Landing page, client dashboard, advocate directory, advocate profile, mobile-first client flow.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Person 3</td><td>Advocate Experience</td><td>Advocate dashboard, profile editing, consultation leads, professional posting shortcut.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Person 4</td><td>Admin + Trust</td><td>Admin dashboard, advocate verification, user management, warnings, moderation controls.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Person 5</td><td>AI Assistant</td><td>AI Q&A, disclaimers, topic suggestions, advocate escalation flow.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Person 6</td><td>Backend/Supabase</td><td>Database schema, RLS policies, seed data, messages, requests, posts, storage planning.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Person 7</td><td>Feed + Social Layer</td><td>Justice feed, post composer, article cards, reactions, comments, report flow.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Person 8</td><td>UI/Polish + Pitch Demo</td><td>Consistent design, responsive layout, empty states, demo script, presentation polish.</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h1>6. Recommended Build Order</h1>
  <ol>
    <li>Auth, roles, and route protection.</li>
    <li>Database schema and seed data.</li>
    <li>Landing page and navigation shell.</li>
    <li>Justice feed with basic posts and article cards.</li>
    <li>Advocate directory.</li>
    <li>Advocate profile page.</li>
    <li>Consultation request flow.</li>
    <li>Client dashboard.</li>
    <li>Advocate dashboard.</li>
    <li>Admin dashboard and verification.</li>
    <li>AI legal learning assistant.</li>
    <li>Messaging inbox.</li>
    <li>Moderation/reporting basics.</li>
    <li>Mobile responsive polish.</li>
    <li>Pitch/demo flow rehearsal.</li>
  </ol>

  <h1>7. Prototype Demo Script</h1>
  <ol>
    <li>Open NyayaSetu landing page and explain the mission: bridge citizens to justice using AI, verified advocates, and a professional justice network.</li>
    <li>Show the justice feed with posts from verified advocates and legal awareness articles.</li>
    <li>Create or open a sample post about tenant rights, consumer complaints, or women safety.</li>
    <li>Ask the AI assistant a legal question in plain language.</li>
    <li>AI explains the issue safely and suggests speaking with an advocate.</li>
    <li>Open the advocate directory and filter by category/city/language.</li>
    <li>Open a verified advocate profile and show credentials, posts, and CTA.</li>
    <li>Send a consultation request.</li>
    <li>Switch to advocate dashboard and accept the lead.</li>
    <li>Switch to admin dashboard and show verification, moderation, and trust controls.</li>
    <li>End with analytics cards showing users, advocates, posts, AI queries, and consultation requests.</li>
  </ol>

  <h1>8. Final Product Direction</h1>
  <p>NyayaSetu should become a justice-focused professional network where people do not come for entertainment but for legal awareness, civic knowledge, professional help, and trusted action. The social layer should not copy LinkedIn or X blindly. It should borrow useful patterns such as profiles, feeds, posts, articles, follows, comments, and professional reputation, but it must add stronger trust through verified advocate badges, moderation, disclaimers, privacy protection, and safe escalation to professional help.</p>
  <p>For the prototype, the highest priority is to make the product feel real, useful, trustworthy, and scalable. The platform should show that one day it can become both a mobile app and desktop platform used by citizens, advocates, law students, NGOs, and institutions across India.</p>
